10155604545325165_10155609585235165	836905499731924	2015-05-06T03:25:50+0000	What prevents the Modi Govt to act progressively on the below ? I am only playing a Devil's advocate to some extent because I am more than convinced that there is no alternative to Modi if we want to save our country from bankruptcy with other sickular parties' clean sweep until 
 the last bit. Maybe Modi need some pressure from public to act and act fast. Also the same kind of mass communication techniques that were used for winning the 2014 Loksabha elections is yet again to be adopted to contain the growing impatience and trust slippage among common man.

1. Improvisation of Aviation sector : What different is Air India/Indian Airlines from where Praful Patel left it almost a year ago ?

2. Sea Ports expansion and improvisation : We do not have a single Port that has undergone improvisation or expansion in the past one year. It has been as motionless as it has been during the UPA era.

3. Coal & Energy sector : Transparent auction process leading to huge income to the Govt. is a true and indisputable fact. But where are the projects of the Govt. directly ? Modi has proved that solar energy harvesting in Gujarat is a great grand success. But as a PM what has he done in the country on unconventional energy resource ? As an impetus for Make in India drive, why can't the Solar harvesting be propagated and encouraged among common man ? I personally thought of investing on Solar energy and if possible give back energy to grid. But what is the encouragement or benefit that I would get in doing so ?

4. Railways : Where on earth has Modi's dream of Bio-toilets, clean and fast train in India gone flying ? Excepting increasing the fare, what visible change are we seeing in the Rail Travel in India ? Even to date we see the porters carrying loads of luggage on their heads reminding us of the Bullocks in our villages. What modernity is brought in to improve the lives of the poor ? 

5. Roads and Infrastructure : Vajapayee ruled our country not for decades, but within the short period he was at the helm,the infra 
 development viz., Road, dams and bridges etc., are numerous and they stand strong even to this moment as proof. What has Gadkari been 
 doing for almost a year now ? Clearing the projects that were cold storaged by congress is not what common man benefits from. In one year is there nothing that can be visible for common man ? Ganga cleaning project - a few ghats in Varanasi are cleaned which is nothing but an iota in the huge Ganga course. 

5. Common man Housing. The monstrous real-estate law has enough ruined the dreams of middle class due to the Builder friendly law that enormously helps the politicians make big bucks. This was the Cong way. But what difference is the common man seeing from Modi Govt. ? Every piece of land in metros like Mumbai & Bangalore are owned and controlled by proxy politician companies. In Bangalore the Builder Mafai has killed the middle-class society. Where is Modi Govt ? Did we vote him with a thumping majority for nothing ?

6. Make In India : Modi seems to be on full thrust of Make In India on the private sector. No doubt this is good and has to happen. But is the Govt not responsible for the improvisation and upgrading of the Public sectors viz., BHEL, HAL, SAIL, ONGC etc., ? Are they not obliged to be first the role model for the rest of the private industries ? By no means any of the public sectors is showing promising results. Is Modi Govt not the custodian of these Public sectors and why is there no impetus of Make in India on PS ?

In my personal opinion the main factors that could possibly stumble Modi Govt are the following. Modi's urgent attention is required.

(a) The stupid principle of "below 65 yrs" limit for the ministers made him keep away the experienced and strong thinkers such as Murali Manohar Joshi, Advani, Yashwant Sinha and Jaswant singh. Instead several inexperienced folks are inducted and asked to handle several strategic and crucial ministries just because they are young. Ideally the young leaders should have shadowed the seniors for a term until they are on their own.

(b) The ultimate Trio (i borrow Shourie's comments) is the limit of grey matter in decision making for this Govt since all others are just by-watchers and seems to have no say whatsover. Is this not another boot-licking/ Jee huzur group just as the predecessor Govt ? 

(c) Full impetus/focus by Modi on Foriegn affairs was very urgenly required for our country since the image of India was brought to the lowest level by the predecessor Govt. So Modi's meeting the leading countries of the world was needed and has been executed brilliantly. But the question is where are the direct tangible benefits of it ? Has the FDI improved ? Has Pak restrained from its usual nonsense ? Has the Bangladeshi infiltration stopped ? Did India move beyond Nepal-Bangaladesh-Sri Lanka boundaries in Trade ? Hence stop going so aggressive on foreign affairs and spend more time in inhouse priorities.

Smriti Irani, Maghrol village, Irani adopted village,Sansad Adarsh Gram Yojana, primary school, Wi-Fi access , ahmedabad news, city news, local news, gujarat news, Indian Express
Union HRD minister Smriti Irani lays foundation stone for various projects at Maghrol village in Anand Monday. (Source: Express Photo)
By: Express News Service | Vadodara | Published on:May 5, 2015 3:30 am	

Union HRD minister Smriti Irani on Monday made a second visit to Maghrol village in Anand district, which she adopted under the Sansad Adarsh Gram Yojana, and gave green signal to projects worth Rs 7.14 crore for the development of the village, which includes tablet PC to each student of the government primary school and Wi-Fi access to the entire village, including the school.

This was Irani’s second visit to the village, over three months after she first visited the village to announce the development plans she had for the residents. Irani has earmarked Rs 42 lakh towards what she has called “smart school project,” which involves tablet PC to each students of the school up to Class VIII at the primary school, Wi-Fi, and basic infrastructure upgradation such as dining hall for mid-day meal, among others, as per announcements made during her January 23 visit.
Related

    Smriti Irani lays foundation stone for development projects in Maghrol village
    Students at Anand village adopted by Smriti Irani to get tablet PC
    Now, Defense Minister plans to develop villages in Rahul's constituency

On Monday, Irani laid the foundations stone for 21 developmental projects in the village that will come up at the cost of Rs 7.14 crore.

She also dedicated an ICU van to the Dharmaj Jalaram Trust and an ambulance to the local government primary health care centre, involving an investment of Rs 1.28 crore. She also distributed 500 health cards to the villagers and inaugurated a doctor-on-call project. Irani also laid foundation stone for two overhead water tank of 5,000 litre capacity each.

“With all these development projects, Maghrol will be the best of all the ideal villages in the country,” she assured the villagers.

Accompanying her was Anand MP Dilipbhai Patel and Anand district administration officers and heads of local governing bodies.

Friday, April 24, 2015

AN APPEAL TO

PRIME MINISTER OF INDIA.

Dear Honorable Respected Prime Minister of India. Shri Narendraji .N. Modiji.

I don’t want my fellow Indian Citizen’s to suffer, at the hands of any builder in future. Kindly look into the matter as you {Prime minister as you have assured me on my face book on the 20th April 2015 @ 12.11 Pm from your prime minister office New Delhi you have written “ aap mujhe report send kare, mai abshya karyawahi karunga”.

I myself would like to humbly put up my case in front of you regarding how I was forced to quit the project xxxx {Name Withheld for security reason, because the builder can kill me or trap me in a false case, as its an universal truth, the fear of a common men, helpless citizen of India, an now its your responsibility to safe guard my life}. As I booked the flat on 28/07/2010 with Rs 10 Lacs as booking amount which the cheque was taken in wrong name they also charged me for 2 car parks @ Rs 2.50 lacs per car park and “ALL” the Maharashtra of ownership Act 1962 {MOFA ACT 1962} were violated, in one of the scheme in Mohamedwadi Pune Flat no A-1001.

When I brought this notices, to the Developer and started communicating vide emails and letters I got the SMS from the owners/directors on the 16/11/2013 “Any more msg to me you may not get your flat as well” which is on records and even threaten me to put behind bars which by email I have communicated with them. My only fault was in asking for my customer rights in term of clean and clear title of my flat.{ As in my case which was “A” building PMC has passed only one flat per floor till 15th of May 2014 As per the challan no CE/BP/2565/14 Receipt no 33820 for Rs-200/- The above records was taken from the PMC as on 15/05/2014, and the builder made extension on the 4th floor as two flats per floor on which I requested him not to construct so I don’t face problem in near future as “CAMPA COLA” of WORLI faced in MUMBI after 24 years .

And then I was forced to quit the project as they threaten me through their lawyer that if you don’t quit we may not give your flat as well which is also on records in form of email transaction, as I am a common men with no roof over my head and I am staying in rented flat since last 26 years and I am all alone, taking care of my 86 years old aged bed ridden paralytic with 85% partially blind orphan maid. I am 53 years Parsee {Zoroastrian} gentlemen staying in pune. So I quitted from the project, as I feared the loss of my hard erne money, I earnestly pray and hope that you both take up my case and this kind of builder should be taken to task I sincerely request that please in future you must see that I don’t get into any trouble or I wont be harm in terms of false implementing me in wrong case or harassment or even builder trying to kill me.

As the builder has settle my payment, it that also he has not paid my due legitimate and also have deprived me of my hard earned interest money, and now after waiting for more then 4 years I am not finding the rate in which I had booked in 2010, for no fault of mine because I asked for my basics customer rights. Its like buyers are beggars and if you asked you get kick, so don’t ask take what we give because we are the ultimatum, who makes the laws of the nation.

And now when I called upon on the 21st April 2015 @ 11.36 Am and spoke to {Name Withheld} the concern person, he even says that “we will not allow you even to buy in any of our projects

across the country” even in resale. (Recorded the conversation for my knowledge.) Is this is Hitlerism/goondanism/ muscle power/or political connection OR they are not worried about the Judiciary system, & law of the nation, as they are fully aware of the loopholes which exits in our judicially systems in our country.

As I have taken this bold step and feel comfortable in your kind esteemed leadership, and after your face book comments I feel comfortable and secured, and hope that I will get a roof over my head and I get once again my flat in A-1001 whenever the builder completes this project.

I hope and pray to both of you to look into my case as I have made 4 journals {correspondences compromise of more then 367 pages} with all records of conversation and emails and letters and telephonic conversation recorded to safe guard my self.

I pray and hope that “Real Estate Regulator bill” comes into enforced with a strong bill, which supports a common men, and one day a common man faces no problems in getting a roof over his head, with a clean and clear market title free from all Illegalities, with basics amenities like clean portable “WATER”. As today I have went through all the turmoil’s, pains, sleepless nights, monetary loss , lost of opportunity, my fundamental constitutional right to have a “roof over my head” & also because of the egoistic issue of the builder

I don’t want my fellow Indian Citizen’s to suffer, at the hands of any builder in future. Kindly look into the matter as you {Prime minister as you have assured me on my face book on the 20th April @ 12.11 Pm from your prime minister office New Delhi you have written “ aap mujhe report send kare, mai abshya karyawahi karunga”

In Solidarity.

Jai Hind.

Humbly yours, Helpless Citizen of India.

Yezdi .F. Motiwalla

motiwallay@yahoo.in

Dear Indian PM Modi,

I would like to thank from the bottom of my heart for the help your country has provided at this time of crisis in my country, Nepal. All the Nepalese in and outside of the country are thankful to your country.

Mr. Modi, Our small country has only one international airport and does not have enough space to land more than 15 planes in a day, Since your quick response on 25th April Saturday, all the Indian planes and helicopters occupied all spaces in our airport ,due to this occupied spaces all the other planes from all over the world carrying emergency medical supplies and food for earthquake victim are waiting to land more than 6 days, and also Nepali people who are flying to Nepal from other countries to visit their home are not able to land because of the landing space in Kathmandu airport is fully occupied by Indian giant planes.

Nepali government officers requested many times to remove Indian planes from our airfield but Indian aircrew team are ignoring request. And also helicopters using by Indian team is only rescuing Indian citizen and ignoring real victims. They are sorting Indian citizen and rescuing only Indian. not delivering any tent, meals,medicine, aid to other victims. Also there is reported that Indian helicopters are hovering on the sensitive areas of Northern part of Nepal Mr. PM Modi,

We have similar culture, identical religion( Though we have many religions) and we understand your National language which is not mean we have to face misbehave from your big country. We are in very critical situation, This is time for save life of victim’s, this is not right time to discriminate or compete with other countries like china or Pakistan, etc. we are very loyal, hard worker and honest people in the world, Our thousands of young people serving in your nation as Gurkha Army Rifles to make safe and save your country. Now in Nepal, there are tons of reporters who came to Nepal from those rescue planes of India are publicize some nonsense news, at least they should follow reporting laws. we need help this time, not photography or video footage.

This is time to give a seat in the helicopter’s to the technical rescue person who can save a life of victim but the reality is Indian reporters are flying everywhere without permission and shooting video of dying people. And also there are many Indian Borders security forces in Kathmandu and others parts of remote areas, why did you send border security forces this time? is there any border issues with Nepal this time? who is responsible for that? Our people desire equal relation with all neighbor’s and surrounding countries. We need help from all friend countries and we respect equally with all. Mr. PM Modi, we are hearty requesting with you, please remove unnecessary planes from our Kathmandu international airport and order your border security forces back to your country. Hope you will understand our problem. Again, I would like to thank you very much for helping us on this crises and looking forward same in the future.

Regards, Nepali People

Just that it sounds same made it people to believe. The Pali canon says Mayadevi is the mother of Buddha. Until 19th century there was no temple dedicated to Mayadevi in Nepal. But there is a temple dedicated to Mayadevi in Konark. It is nearly 1000 years old. Even the first disciples of Buddha were Tapasu and Bhalika - two merchants from Kalinga. Kalinga was a Buddhist state 2000 years ago..The last remains of Buddha are buried in Pushpagiri. Buddha's tooth relic was found in Dantapura...now Puri.. There was no Lumbini in the map of Nepal until Anton Führer forged the rock edict..

For those who are Inviting your Friends to this page: Here is an easy Tips 
1. Select Invite button and choose Friends
2. If you have more friends, The default selected and suggested tab won’t have "SELECT ALL" Enabled and doing manually will take time.
3. So click Area, Group or Event at left hand side, And you will see SELECT ALL function which allows to invite 100 Friends at once.
4. If you select past events at left, Click "All Guests" on top to show more lists.
5. Repeat to Invite all friends to spread this message to all.
Hope It will be helpful. Pls comment if any confusion.
